<div>
<head>The manuscript</head>
<p>Cardiff Free Library 2.83 (= Cardiff MS 6)</p>
<p>Manuscript description in <hi rend="italic">Report on Manuscripts in the Welsh Language</hi><!--vol?-->, p. 104:
<quote><hi rend="smallcaps">Miscellanea</hi>, containing 'Historical' and Moral <hi rend="smallcaps"><hi rend="italic">Triads</hi></hi>, the <hi rend="italic">Interpretation of Dreams</hi>, the 'Histories' of the <hi rend="italic">Dog-star</hi>, of <hi rend="smallcaps"><hi rend="italic">Tristan</hi></hi> and <hi rend="smallcaps"><hi rend="italic">Esyllt</hi></hi>, of the <hi rend="italic">Seven Wise Men of Rome</hi>, Religious <hi rend="italic">plays</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Dialogues</hi>, in verse, between <hi rend="italic">Body and Soul</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Arthur and Eliwlod</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">king</hi> and his <hi rend="italic">servant</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">Young Man</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Wren</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Eiry Mynydd</hi>, selected sayings and passages from 'Dionysius' Cato, Seneca, Marcus Aurelius, etc. Paper; 7&frac34; x 5&frac34; inches; 190 pages, stained and imperfect in many places, especially at the corners and margins which have been clumsily covered with tracing paper; <hi rend="italic">circa</hi> 1550; bound in morocco.</quote></p>
<p>Unfortunately, several pages have been lost in the meantime, cf. <hi rend="italic">Summary Catalogue of the Manuscripts of South Glamorgan Libraries, Cardiff Central Library [...]</hi>, compiled by Graham C.G. Thomas and Daniel Huws, Aberystwyth: National Library of Wales, 1995, p. 84:
<quote>pp. 130-54 and 163-6 were wanting when the MS was seen in 1978. It was then in a half-leather modern binding by W H Smith.</quote>
Among the texts lost are <hi rend="italic">Y brenin ar gwas</hi> and the Triads.</p>
</div>
